    Note over Alice,Network: ═══════════ ITERATION 1: ALLOCATION (Two-Phase) ═══════════
    Note over Alice,Network: 📐 structure.md uses TWO-PHASE allocation:<br/>Phase 1 = Reciprocal relationships (priority)<br/>Phase 2 = Unilateral priority (remaining capacity)

    par Parallel Allocation (Providers compute independently)
        rect rgb(255, 248, 240)
            Note over Carol: 🔄 TWO-PHASE ALLOCATION ALGORITHM
            Carol->>Carol: Phase 1: Priority Alignment<br/>  Check for Reciprocal-Alignment > 0<br/>  → None! (Carol doesn't recognize anyone)<br/>  → No Phase 1 allocations<br/><br/>Phase 2: Unilateral Priority<br/>  RemainingCapacity = 150 - 0 = 150<br/><br/>  Unilateral recipients:<br/>    Alice: ShareTotal_Carol→Alice = 0 (no recognition)<br/>    Bob: ShareTotal_Carol→Bob = 0 (no recognition)<br/><br/>  ⚠️ Carol can't allocate (no recognition of recipients)<br/>  💡 This is ONE-WAY recognition scenario
            Carol->>Network: Publish Allocations: []<br/>(No allocations - Carol doesn't recognize recipients)
        end
    and
        rect rgb(255, 248, 240)
            Note over Kitchen: 🔄 TWO-PHASE ALLOCATION ALGORITHM
            Kitchen->>Kitchen: Phase 1: Priority Alignment<br/>  Check for Reciprocal-Alignment > 0<br/>  → None! (Kitchen doesn't recognize anyone)<br/>  → No Phase 1 allocations<br/><br/>Phase 2: Unilateral Priority<br/>  RemainingCapacity = 200 - 0 = 200<br/><br/>  Unilateral recipients:<br/>    Alice: ShareTotal_Kitchen→Alice = 0<br/>    Bob: ShareTotal_Kitchen→Bob = 0<br/><br/>  ⚠️ Kitchen can't allocate (no recognition)<br/>  💡 Providers need to recognize recipients!
            Kitchen->>Network: Publish Allocations: []<br/>(No allocations - Kitchen doesn't recognize recipients)
        end
