    Note over Alice,Network: ═══════════ ITERATION 2: ALLOCATION (With Reciprocal Alignment) ═══════════
    Note over Alice,Network: 📐 Now both Phases will work!

    par Parallel Two-Phase Allocation (With Reciprocal Alignment)
        rect rgb(220, 240, 255)
            Note over Carol: 🔄 TWO-PHASE ALLOCATION (Complete)
            Carol->>Carol: Phase 1: Priority Alignment<br/>  Recipients with RA > 0:<br/>    Alice: RA = 0.429<br/>    Bob: RA = 0.571<br/>  Total RA = 1.0<br/><br/>  PriorityShare_Alice = 0.429 / 1.0 = 0.429<br/>  PriorityShare_Bob = 0.571 / 1.0 = 0.571<br/><br/>  RawAllocation_Alice = 150 × 0.429 = 64.3<br/>  RawAllocation_Bob = 150 × 0.571 = 85.7<br/><br/>  FinalAllocation_Alice = min(64.3, 100) = 64.3<br/>  FinalAllocation_Bob = min(85.7, 90) = 85.7<br/><br/>Phase 2: Unilateral Priority<br/>  RemainingCapacity = 150 - 150 = 0<br/>  → No Phase 2 allocations (all capacity used)<br/><br/>✅ Both recipients served via Phase 1!
            Carol->>Network: Publish Allocations {<br/>  [{to: Alice, qty: 64.3, phase: "priority"},<br/>   {to: Bob, qty: 85.7, phase: "priority"}]<br/>}
        end
    and
        rect rgb(220, 240, 255)
            Note over Kitchen: 🔄 TWO-PHASE ALLOCATION (Complete)
            Kitchen->>Kitchen: Phase 1: Priority Alignment<br/>  Recipients with RA > 0:<br/>    Alice: RA = 0.4<br/>    Bob: RA = 0.429<br/>  Total RA = 0.829<br/><br/>  PriorityShare_Alice = 0.4 / 0.829 = 0.482<br/>  PriorityShare_Bob = 0.429 / 0.829 = 0.518<br/><br/>  RawAllocation_Alice = 200 × 0.482 = 96.4<br/>  RawAllocation_Bob = 200 × 0.518 = 103.6<br/><br/>  FinalAllocation_Alice = min(96.4, 100) = 96.4<br/>  FinalAllocation_Bob = min(103.6, 90) = 90<br/><br/>Phase 2: Unilateral Priority<br/>  RemainingCapacity = 200 - 186.4 = 13.6<br/>  → No unilateral recipients<br/>  → 13.6 capacity remains unused<br/><br/>✅ All priority recipients satisfied!
