    Note over Alice,Network: ═══════════ RECIPIENTS OBSERVE PROVIDER SATISFACTION ═══════════
    Note over Alice,Network: 🔄 Recipients reactively update their ShareOfGeneralSatisfaction

    par Parallel Share Recomputation (Recipients observe provider satisfaction)
        rect rgb(255, 240, 255)
            Note over Alice: 📊 RECOMPUTE ShareOfGeneralSatisfaction
            Alice->>Alice: Observe provider satisfaction from network:<br/>  Carol: root.satisfaction = 0.665<br/>  Kitchen: root.satisfaction = 0.921<br/><br/>Recompute ShareOfGeneralSatisfaction:<br/><br/>Step 1: Calculate influence pools<br/>  Non-Slot node weight: 1.0<br/>  Non-Slot satisfaction: (now uses slot data)<br/>  P_total = 1.0 × weighted_sat<br/><br/>Step 3: Calculate raw shares (satisfaction-weighted!)<br/>  Carol: (1.0 × 0.665) × (30/50) = 0.399<br/>  Kitchen: (1.0 × 0.921) × (20/50) = 0.368<br/>  Total = 0.767<br/><br/>Step 4: Normalize<br/>  Carol: 0.399 / 0.767 = 0.520<br/>  Kitchen: 0.368 / 0.767 = 0.480<br/><br/>💡 Shares adjusted based on satisfaction!
            Note over Alice: DerivedStateMap[Alice] updated:<br/>Carol share: 0.6 → 0.520 (DOWN)<br/>Kitchen share: 0.4 → 0.480 (UP!)
        end
    and
        rect rgb(255, 240, 255)
            Note over Bob: 📊 RECOMPUTE ShareOfGeneralSatisfaction
            Bob->>Bob: Observe provider satisfaction:<br/>  Carol: 0.665<br/>  Kitchen: 0.921<br/><br/>Recompute shares (satisfaction-weighted):<br/>  Carol: (1.0 × 0.665) × (40/70) = 0.379<br/>  Kitchen: (1.0 × 0.921) × (30/70) = 0.395<br/>  Total = 0.774<br/><br/>Normalize:<br/>  Carol: 0.379 / 0.774 = 0.490 (DOWN from 0.571!)<br/>  Kitchen: 0.395 / 0.774 = 0.510 (UP from 0.429!)<br/><br/>💡 Quality matters! Kitchen's high satisfaction<br/>increased their share despite lower recognition!
            Note over Bob: DerivedStateMap[Bob] updated:<br/>Carol share: 0.571 → 0.490 (DOWN)<br/>Kitchen share: 0.429 → 0.510 (UP!)
        end
