    Note over Alice,Network: ═══════════ ARCHITECTURE PRINCIPLES ═══════════

    rect rgb(240, 240, 255)
        Note over Alice,Network: 🏗️ STRUCTURE.MD ARCHITECTURE:<br/><br/>1. SEPARATION OF USER-INPUT & DERIVED STATE:<br/>   📝 Tree = User inputs (stable, serializable)<br/>      - Points, contributors, needs, capacities<br/>      - Only changes when user explicitly edits<br/>   <br/>   📊 DerivedStateMap = Computed values (reactive, ephemeral)<br/>      - Weights, shares, satisfaction, allocations<br/>      - Recomputes automatically on tree changes<br/>      - Keyed by node_id for O(1) lookup<br/>      - Can be reconstructed from trees<br/><br/>2. REACTIVE COMPUTATION FLOW:<br/>   User Edit → Tree Update (inputs only)<br/>       ↓<br/>   Dependency Analysis<br/>       ↓<br/>   Mark Affected States Dirty<br/>       ↓<br/>   Parallel Recomputation<br/>       ↓<br/>   Update DerivedStateMap<br/>       ↓<br/>   UI Reactively Updates<br/><br/>3. HIERARCHICAL SATISFACTION AGGREGATION:<br/>   Allocation satisfaction (recipient rates)<br/>       ↓ (weighted by accepted quantity)<br/>   Need-Slot satisfaction<br/>       ↓ (weighted by child weights)<br/>   Capacity-Slot satisfaction<br/>       ↓ (weighted by child weights)<br/>   Goal satisfaction<br/>       ↓ (weighted by child weights)<br/>   Root satisfaction<br/>   <br/>   💡 Each level dampens individual variance<br/>   💡 Prevents single allocation from dominating<br/><br/>4. SHAREOFGENERALSATISFACTION (4 Steps):<br/>   Step 1: Calculate influence pools (weighted by tree)<br/>   Step 2: Calculate recognition pools (positive/anti)<br/>   Step 3: Calculate raw shares (per contributor)<br/>   Step 4: Apply pool-bounded recognition (normalize)<br/>   <br/>   Result: Comprehensive recognition across entire tree<br/>   Supports: Anti-contributors, weighted nodes, hierarchies<br/><br/>5. TWO-PHASE ALLOCATION:<br/>   Phase 1: Reciprocal-Alignment > 0 (priority access)<br/>      - Both parties recognize each other<br/>      - Gets first pick of capacity<br/>   <br/>   Phase 2: Unilateral priority (remaining capacity)<br/>      - One-way recognition<br/>      - Only gets leftovers after Phase 1<br/>   <br/>   💡 Incentivizes reciprocal relationships<br/><br/>6. STABILITY GUARANTEES:<br/>   ✓ Bounded state space (satisfaction ∈ [0,1])<br/>   ✓ Time delay (satisfaction after allocation)<br/>   ✓ Hierarchical dampening (tree aggregation)<br/>   ✓ Per-type adaptive damping (α_k)<br/>   ✓ Min function (conservative MS)<br/>   ✓ Need caps (no unbounded growth)<br/>   ✓ Network penalties (gaming resistance)
    end

